-You two!

934
01:37:29,600 --> 01:37:31,500
Hold back! Hold your fire!

935
01:37:31,700 --> 01:37:34,400
Get the building secure.

936
01:37:34,600 --> 01:37:36,100
Give me the gun.

937
01:37:36,300 --> 01:37:40,700
-l don't want to shoot you.
-You do. You think l deserve it.

938
01:37:40,900 --> 01:37:44,200
-Get back!
-But you won't. lt's not the real you.

939
01:37:44,400 --> 01:37:48,100
-You don't know anything about me.
-l do. You're my kid.

940
01:37:48,200 --> 01:37:52,000
You're not a bad kid. You're a scared kid
whose old man left him.

941
01:37:52,200 --> 01:37:58,000
You didn't get a choice and it hurt. l know.
But you're my son. You always will be.

942
01:37:58,200 --> 01:37:59,800
Then why did you leave?

943
01:38:00,000 --> 01:38:03,600
l was stupid. l forgot
what it felt like to be alone.

944
01:38:03,800 --> 01:38:08,800
You don't want to do to Angelo what
l did to you. What my old man did to me.

945
01:38:09,000 --> 01:38:11,500
-You can't.
-He don't need a junkie.

946
01:38:11,700 --> 01:38:15,900
You're not a junkie to him.
My old man wasn't a killer to me.

947
01:38:16,200 --> 01:38:20,800
When my old man left, l hated him
all my life for what he did to me.

948
01:38:21,000 --> 01:38:25,900
But all l wanted was for him to walk
in the door because l missed him.

949
01:38:26,100 --> 01:38:28,600
l didn't want to be alone
anymore.

950
01:38:28,800 --> 01:38:32,700
We all pay a price for what we do,
but when's enough?

951
01:38:33,000 --> 01:38:37,100
Because l paid. And you paid. And what?
Now Angelo has to pay?

952
01:38:37,200 --> 01:38:41,800
You can't! We got a second chance
here, me and you.

953
01:38:42,000 --> 01:38:44,900
l let you think
you didn't matter to me.

954
01:38:45,200 --> 01:38:47,500
But l swear l won't run away again.

955
01:38:47,700 --> 01:38:51,900
l'll stay with you, l promise.
You just need to choose it.

956
01:38:52,100 --> 01:38:55,300
Know how many people
would love a second chance?

957
01:39:03,200 --> 01:39:04,800
Help me.

958
01:39:20,700 --> 01:39:24,100
-Dad, are you okay?
-lt's just my shoulder.

959
01:39:25,900 --> 01:39:28,200
-l didn't do it.
-l know.

960
01:39:29,700 --> 01:39:31,200
Get rid of the guns!

961
01:39:31,400 --> 01:39:34,600
Empty your pockets.
Don't give them an excuse.

962
01:39:34,800 --> 01:39:38,000
-They'll kill me.
-lt's okay. l'm with you now.

963
01:39:38,400 --> 01:39:39,900
ldentify yourself!

964
01:39:40,200 --> 01:39:41,900
lt's okay.

965
01:39:43,400 --> 01:39:46,300
lt's okay, there are no guns!
Raise your hands.

966
01:39:46,500 --> 01:39:48,300
See the hands? No guns.

967
01:39:48,500 --> 01:39:52,400
-Get down, drop the gun!
-Show us your hands!

968
01:39:52,600 --> 01:39:54,200
-They're down.
-Move away!

969
01:39:54,400 --> 01:39:55,800
Move away from him!

970
01:39:56,000 --> 01:39:58,600
-Told you to move away!
-Take it easy.

971
01:39:58,700 --> 01:40:00,800
All right, take it easy on him!

972
01:40:01,000 --> 01:40:05,200
Listen! Anything happens to him,
you'll answer to me.

973
01:40:05,400 --> 01:40:06,700
Easy with him!

974
01:40:06,900 --> 01:40:08,500
lt'll be all right.

975
01:40:08,700 --> 01:40:11,400
lt's okay, son. lt's okay.

976
01:40:23,100 --> 01:40:24,500
Here he comes.

977
01:40:24,700 --> 01:40:26,200
This way.

978
01:40:37,700 --> 01:40:39,300
Watch your head.

979
01:40:51,400 --> 01:40:53,700
I love you.

980
01:41:32,100 --> 01:41:34,500
l want to go on the rocks.

981
01:41:34,700 --> 01:41:37,900
Yeah, those are the rocks.
That's the jetty.

982
01:41:39,400 --> 01:41:41,700
Let's go on the rocks.

983
01:41:41,900 --> 01:41:45,100
Yeah, those are the rocks.

984
01:41:46,600 --> 01:41:49,400
Look, see that?

985
01:41:49,600 --> 01:41:52,600
You see that, the airplane? See?

986
01:41:52,900 --> 01:41:55,700
-Where do you think that's going?
-Flying....

987
01:41:57,500 --> 01:42:01,500
You want to fly away
with your dad sometime? Yeah?

988
01:42:01,700 --> 01:42:05,300
Because he wants to go with you.
He told me so.

989
01:42:05,600 --> 01:42:09,900
He told me he wants to take you
to Key West.

990
01:42:10,100 --> 01:42:12,700
You wanna go?
Yeah? Good.

991
01:42:12,900 --> 01:42:16,500
When he comes back,
you'll go with him to Key West.

992
01:42:17,900 --> 01:42:19,900
Me, you and him.

993
01:42:21,500 --> 01:42:26,400
Grandpa, Daddy and you.
We're gonna go to Key West.

994
01:42:26,900 --> 01:42:28,400
-Okay?
-Yeah.

995
01:42:28,600 --> 01:42:30,400
Okay, sweetheart.

996
01:42:32,800 --> 01:42:35,600
You want to put the water
in the thing?

997
01:42:35,800 --> 01:42:38,000
Go put the water in the thing.

